    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Instead of using <code>FileWriter</code>, create a <code>FileOutputStream</code>. You can then wrap this in an <code>OutputStreamWriter</code>, which allows you to pass an encoding in the constructor. Then you can write your data to that inside a <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/exceptions/tryResourceClose.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">try-with-resources Statement</a>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>try (OutputStreamWriter writer =\n             new OutputStreamWriter(new FileOutputStream(PROPERTIES_FILE), StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\n    // do stuff\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
