    "creation_date" : 1458770280,
    "answer_id" : 36189491,
    "question_id" : 1001540,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Below sample code can read file line by line and write new file in UTF-8 format. Also, i am explicitly specifying Cp1252 encoding.</p>\n\n<pre><code>    public static void main(String args[]) throws IOException {\n\n    BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(\n            new FileInputStream(\"c:\\\\filenonUTF.txt\"),\n            \"Cp1252\"));\n    String line;\n\n    Writer out = new BufferedWriter(\n            new OutputStreamWriter(new FileOutputStream(\n                    \"c:\\\\fileUTF.txt\"), \"UTF-8\"));\n\n    try {\n\n        while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {\n\n            out.write(line);\n            out.write(\"\\n\");\n\n        }\n\n    } finally {\n\n        br.close();\n        out.close();\n\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
