    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here is an example of writing UTF-8 characters in the Eclipse IDE and to a File.</p>\n<p>For Eclipse.simply set the Encoding to UTF-8 from <strong><code>Run -&gt;  Run Configurations -&gt; Common</code></strong>\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/me3O4.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Common Dialog</a></p>\n<pre><code>import java.io.BufferedWriter;\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.FileOutputStream;\nimport java.io.OutputStreamWriter;\n\npublic class UTF_8_Example {\n\n    /**\n     * Example of printing UTF-8 characters inside Eclipse IDE and a File.\n     * &lt;p&gt;\n     * For eclipse, you must go to Run -&gt;  Run Configurations -&gt; Common \n     * and set Encoding to UTF-8.\n     * &lt;p&gt;\n     * @param args\n     */\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        BufferedWriter writer = null;\n\n        try {\n            ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\n            // WRITE UTF-8 WITHIN ECLIPSE EDITOR\n            ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////         \n            char character = '►';\n            int code = character;\n            char hex = '\\u25ba';\n            String value = &quot;[&quot; + Integer.toHexString(code) + &quot;][\\u25ba][&quot; + character + &quot;][&quot; + (char)code + &quot;][&quot; + hex + &quot;]&quot;;\n            System.out.println(value);\n\n            ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\n            // WRITE UTF-8 TO A FILE\n            ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\n            File file = new File(&quot;UTF_8_EXAMPLE.TXT&quot;);\n            FileOutputStream fileOutputStream = new FileOutputStream(file);\n            OutputStreamWriter outputStreamWriter = new OutputStreamWriter(fileOutputStream, &quot;UTF-8&quot;);\n            writer = new BufferedWriter(outputStreamWriter);\n            writer.write(value);\n        }\n        catch(Throwable e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n        finally {\n            try {\n                if(writer != null) { writer.close(); }\n            }\n            catch(Throwable e) {\n                throw new RuntimeException(e);              \n            }\n        }\n    }   \n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
